findings.lungs: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.
findings.liver: Homogenous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. Gallbladder within normal limits.
findings.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
findings.kidneys: Normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. No focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
findings.appendix: Enlarged and hyperemic measuring up to 9 mm with minimal adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute uncomplicated appendicitis.
findings.gastrointestinal: Stomach unremarkable. Large duodenum diverticulum. Normal caliber, wall thickness, and enhancement of small bowel loops.
findings.pelvis: Urinary bladder and distal ureters unremarkable. No free fluid in the pelvis.
findings.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
findings.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
findings.soft tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall within normal limits.
